<item>
            <title>[LU-19957] __ll_page_mkwrite() redundant check</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19957</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;smatch highlights this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; if (result == 0) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; lock_page(vmpage);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; if (vmpage-&amp;gt;mapping == NULL) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; unlock_page(vmpage);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; /* page was truncated and lock was cancelled, return
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;* ENODATA so that VM_FAULT_NOPAGE will be returned
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;* to handle_mm_fault().
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;*/
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; if (result == 0)
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; result = -ENODATA;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;the result is checked twice for no reason.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem introduced by this patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/5222&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/5222&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
